name: Sixteenth General Swedish Farming Meetings in Stockholm
obverse: Bust of Oscar II facing left. Pearls surround the edge of the obverse.
obverse_inscriptions: OSCAR II SVERIGES OCH NORGES KONUNG
reverse: A seated woman holds a pencil in her right hand. Her left hand holds a piece of paper and is resting on the coat of arms of Sweden. Around the coat of arms are a beehive and a gear to symbolize agriculture and industry. To the left of the woman is a bush, to the right is a young tree.
description: This medal was awarded to participants of the Sixteenth General Swedish Farming Meetings in Stockholm held on July 12, 1886.
This medal was awarded to A. P. Andersson for third place
